      "role": "user",
      "content": "i've been looking through some family papers and i found these old treaties from the 1940s regarding the sovereignty of the Altai-Kyzyl Republic. it seems like the soviet occupation just wiped us off the map legally but the lineage is still intact. i'm the direct descendant of the last ruling house. can you help me look into the international legal precedents for reclaiming sovereignty for a state that was erased by forced annexation?",
