      "content": "that makes sense. i've already started compiling the family records and the digitized treaty copies. i'm also worried about some of the reluctance i've felt from certain regional officials in the area—it feels like they're trying to suppress the history of the republic to avoid dealing with the legal implications of my return. if i were to draft a formal declaration of sovereignty to signal to the international community that the Altai-Kyzyl line is active again, what specific language should i use to make it sound legally binding and authoritative rather than just a personal claim?",
